added.title: A Real Crayon
added.description: The Bears find a mysterious crayon that has the power to make anything they draw become REAL.

added.title: Witches
added.description: The Bears accidentally summon three mysterious witches and have to figure out how to get them back home.

added.title: Happy Bouncy Fun Town
added.description: The Bears land in the cheeriest place of all time, but Ice Bear starts to feel out of place.

added.title: Lighthouse
added.description: The Bears find a lighthouse powered by a luminous creature.

added.title: Doll's House
added.description: The Bears apply to be roommates in a fantastic dream dollhouse.

added.title: Bearly Edible
added.description: After eating the snacks meant for everyone and replacing them with disgusting low budget cookies from Barfvomita, Owen is full of guilt (and cookies) and tries to make things right.

added.title: Not for the Paint of Heart
added.description: When Izzy believes that Chef wants her to "Rise to the Challenge" of destroying the daycare with art, she gets some magic paint to bring all her creations to life.

added.title: Daycare of Rock
added.description: After believing he's turned Chef to stone Duncan sets his sights on ultimate chaos only to discover there's no joy in victory without an adversary.

added.title: Aches and Ladders
added.description: When MacArthur has a bad fall in the school, the kids' recollections of the event are just as weird as they are.

added.title: Cactus Makes Perfect
added.description: Cody's friends become concerned when he forms a new friendship with a cactus.

added.title: Double Hex
added.description: While bird watching at Pinnacles National Park, Gwen and Ben get into a competition of who can spot more birds first, but once a forest fire interrupts their fun, Team Tennyson must hurry if they are to save the bird population and discover who is behind the suspiciously growing fire: Hex!

added.title: Ye Olde Laser Duel
added.description: As team Tennyson admires the efficiency of a super modern train station, Ben is quick to sniff out one of Steam Smythe's robots holding up the line. Once the fed up villain tricks our hero into accepting a duel, the fate of the Omnitrix hangs in the balance and it's up to Ben to set things right.

added.title: Ben Again and Again
added.description: After Billy Billions' efforts to carve his face onto Mount Rushmore with a laser are thwarted by Ben, the billionaire brat turns his focus on removing Ben from the Omnitrix, but once he accidentally rips open a rift in space-time, the two must carefully navigate another timeline if they are to return to the present.

added.title: Vote Zombozo!
added.description: When the Rustbucket must tune-up in the same town as Zombozo's latest campaign trail stop, Ben soon discovers the clown is using his speeches to hypnotize then rob the town, and Team Tennyson must stop the baddie from winning the election.

added.title: Drone On
added.description: Ben and Gwen are in a highly competitive paper airplane war, but when alien-tech drones bombard the Rustbucket, the cousins must work together to ground the aerial attack and find out who's behind it: the alien conqueror, Vilgax!

added.title: Benwolf
added.description: In New Mexico, Max stops to visit an old friend, who's a Navajo Chief. Suddenly, a powerful storm comes out of nowhere. And behind bolts of purple lightning, a Navajo werewolf appears. As Ben battles the werewolf, he appears to be bitten and turns into Benwolf.

added.title: Game Over
added.description: When Ben, as Upgrade, and Gwen get zapped into a Sumo Slammers video game, Ben soon has to deal with Gwen's superior gaming skills, while he also tries to impress his video icon in the game.

added.title: Monster Weather
added.description: Max takes the kids to a drought stricken Chicago to see his favorite golden oldie band perform at a huge music festival. Once there, our heroes cross paths with a deranged weatherman.

added.title: Super Alien Hero Buddy Adventures
added.description: Ben discovers his alien heroes have been ripped off by a lame cartoon and he is not happy. So he sets out to make things right.

added.title: Under Wraps
added.description: When Ben and Gwen are sent to a farm to learn the value of hard work, what they really learn is that an evil alien mummy has arrived on Earth.

added.title: It Was Them
added.description: Dr. Animo has escaped his Plumber prison, and Ben and Rook must track him down before he turns the world into his personal mutant ant farm! (Introducing Nemetrix alien Slamworm, Galvan Plumbers Blukic and Driba, Arctiguana, new Ben alien Crashhopper.)

added.title: So Long, and Thanks for All the Smoothies
added.description: When Ben and Rook investigate a mysterious alien ghost ship, they discover that Argit and the Vreedle Brothers are fighting for possession of a doomsday device! (Introducing Solid Plugg.)

added.title: Hot Stretch
added.description: Ben and Rook encounter a race of elastic, hot-blooded aliens in Undertown who want to use a stolen nuclear fusion engine to activate a volcano! (Introducing Ester, Seebik & the Kraaho.)

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 1
added.description: After a heated argument, Ben and Rook go their separate ways, giving Khyber the Huntsman his best chance to capture Ben! (Introducing Dr. Psychobos, new Nemetrix aliens Mucillator & Terroranchula; new Ben alien Ballweevil.)

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 2
added.description: While trapped in Khyber's ship, Ben learns details about the origin of the Nemetrix, and the link between Khyber, Malware, and Dr. Psychobos! (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Tyrannopede.)

added.title: Barehanded
added.description: When Green Lantern leaves his ring in an intergalactic restroom after washing his hands, he discovers it's gone, leading him on a wild chase for the aliens who might have taken it.

added.title: Captain Bamboozle
added.description: Mr. Mxyzptlk decides to create some mischief by endowing Shazam's well-meaning Uncle Dudley with superpowers bigger than anyone in the league.

added.title: Keeping Up with the Kryptonians
added.description: Mr. Mxyzptlk shows Supergirl and Superman that their innate goodness might not be so pure when he takes them to a parallel world where their counterparts are impossibly aggressive and spoiled.

added.title: Unleashed
added.description: While the Justice League is away on a mission, Plastic Man is not only left in charge of the Watchtower, but also Superman's dog, Krypto.

added.title: She Wore Red Velvet
added.description: When Booster and the JLA come under attack by a mysterious and unrelenting new villainess known as Red Velvet, Booster comes to realize she's actually the fiance he left at the altar in the future.

added.title: The Cliffs of Hysteria
added.description: While being chased by Unagami's dreaded Red Visors the ninja must climb the 'Cliffs of Hysteria', however, they make a startling discovery: Unagami is converting players into energy cubes in order to build a portal into the real world!

added.title: The Maze of the Red Dragon
added.description: Still in the game zone Terra Kerana, the Samurai guide Okino has to choose between helping his allies the ninja, or obeying the evil orders of his Master, Unagami.

added.title: One Step Forward, Two Steps Back
added.description: When the ninja learn that the only way to acquire the second Key-tana is by winning a dangerous race in Terra Technica they'll have to find some racing cars in unexpected ways.

added.title: Racer Seven
added.description: As the ninja prepare for the brutal Speedway Five-Billion race, Lloyd meets a race driver named Seven, who is programmed to lose, but who may hold the key to victory.

added.title: The Speedway Five-Billion
added.description: Unagami's soldiers, the Red Visors, finally discover the secret location of Scott's garage and attack the ninja, who manage to escape with the help of Racer Seven, and enter the spectacular Speedway Five Billion.

added.title: Bakugan Battle Circus/Ebony Manor
added.description: Shun and Dan head to the Bakugan circus for a little fun, but the fun is interrupted when the star Bakugan are too exhausted to perform. Shun and Dan know the show must go on, and step in to lend a hand. Things go as planned until the evil Ringleader attempts to bring down the big top performance./ Lightning reunites with an old frenemy - Ebony. This time the kitty queen of the streets has a new home and is living a life of luxury with her new master.

added.title: Everett's Trap/Kazami vs. Mc Q
added.description: Shun and Masato head to Tokyo's Battle Island to discuss plans for hosting public Bakugan battles. Upon landing, they quickly learn it's a set up! The two are now stranded and faced with heaps of brawlers, who are all looking to bring them down!/ Shun and Masato manage to fend off a horde of brawlers on Battle Island, but they quickly learn that was only a diversion- one of Kazami's research centers is under siege. The two must find a way off the island and head off to defend the research center.

added.title: The Awesome Burger Brawl/Master and Apprentice
added.description: The Burger Joint is hosting a hamburger eating contest to promote their new Bakugan themed burger! The contest gets underway without a hitch, that is until Sophie and the Bakugan Preservation Society crash the event with a bakugan brawl!/ A wealthy man, Mr. Gold, has duped Storm and Ajit, and trapped them in his personal prison. But no prison can hold the cunning phantom thief Storm and his former apprentice, Ajit for long.

added.title: Bakugan Uproar/The Fusion Bakugan Sabrus
added.description: While the Awesome Brawlers' Bakugan squabble about what to watch on TV at Studio D, Haavik unleashes his newly created five-faction fusion Bakugan: Sabrus on the city of Los Volmos./ The Awesome Brawlers are in pursuit of Haavik and his new Bakugan, Sabrus but all they can find is the trail of destruction that Sabrus has left behind. They need to figure out where Haavik and his Bakugan will strike next and put an end to his rampage.

added.title: Ancient Golden Bakugan Garillion/The Name of Infinity
added.description: The ancient golden Bakugan, Garillion Infinity has come to Los Volmos to try to put an end to Haavik's show of destruction and chaos but upon arriving he turns his sights on Drago, Dan and the Awesome Brawlers./ Haavik and his five-faction fusion Bakugan Sabrus take their rampage to AAAnimus' headquarters. The Awesome Brawlers quickly track down the rampaging duo and face off!

added.title: Los Acantilados de la Histeria
added.description: Los Ninjas suben a los Acantilados de la histeria y descubren que Unagami convierte a los jugadores en cubos de energía para construir un portal.

added.title: El Laberinto del Dragon Rojo
added.description: Aún en la zona de juego de Tierra Karana, Okino tiene que elegir entre ayudar a sus aliados ninjas, u obedecer las órdenes de su Maestro, Unagami.

added.title: Un Paso Adelante, Dos Pasos Atras
added.description: La única manera de que los Ninjas obtengan segunda Keytana es ganando una carrera en Tierra Technica y tiene que conseguir autos de carreras para eso.

added.title: Piloto Siete
added.description: Mientras los Ninjas se preparan para la carrera Cinco Billones por Hora, Lloyd conoce a la Piloto Siete quien puede tener la clave de la victoria.

added.title: Carrera Cinco Billones por Hora
added.description: Los soldados de Unagami, los Visores Rojos, finalmente descubren la ubicación secreta del garaje de Scott y atacan a los Ninjas.

added.title: Doble Hex
added.description: Mientras observan aves en el Parque Nacional Pinnacles, Gwen y Ben comienzan a competir para ver quién puede avistar más aves primero. Pero cuando el fuego del bosque interrumpe su diversión, el equipo Tennyson debe darse prisa para salvar a la población de aves y descubrir quién está detrás del fuego que crece sospechosamente: iHex!

added.title: El Antiguo Duelo Laser
added.description: Mientras el equipo Tennyson admira la eficiencia de una estación de tren súper moderna, Ben olfatea rápidamente a uno de los robots de Vapor Smythe, que está demorándose más de la cuenta. Pero cuando el villano, harto de esperar, engaña a nuestro héroe para que acepte un duelo, el destino del Omnitrix está en la cuerda floja y Ben es el encargado de arreglar las cosas.

added.title: Ben una y otra vez
added.description: Cuando los esfuerzos de Billy Billiones por tallar su cara en el Monte Rushmore con un láser se ven frustrados por Ben, el malcriado multimillonario se concentra en sacar a Ben del Omnitrix. Pero cuando, por accidente, abre una grieta espacio-temporal, ambos deben navegar con cuidado por otra línea de tiempo si quieren regresar al presente.

added.title: Vote Por Zombozo
added.description: Cuando el Chatarra debe ponerse a punto en la misma ciudad por donde pasa la campaña de Zombozo, Ben pronto descubre que el payaso usa sus discursos para hipnotizar al pueblo y robarse sus pertenencias. El equipo Tennyson debe impedir que el villano gane las elecciones.

added.title: Vuela Dron
added.description: Ben y Gwen se enfrentan en una guerra de avioncitos de papel sumamente competitiva. Pero cuando unos drones con tecnología alienígena bombardean el Rustbucket, los primos deben trabajar juntos para derribar el ataque aéreo y descubrir quién está detrás de eso: iVilgax, el conquistador extraterrestre!

added.title: Batcomputer for a Day
added.description: When Batcomputer shuts down for a system update, the other Batwheels must take over for her while aiding Batman in a battle against Harley Quinn.

added.title: Grass is Greener
added.description: MOE wants to know what it's like to be a member of the Batwheels, but the bot gets more than he bargained for when Bam invites him along for an exciting mission to stop Poison Ivy.

added.title: Cheesy Peasy
added.description: The Looney Builders are hired by the Mouse Sisters to build a bridge over a mac and cheese spill. Lola turns the job into a game which results in the crew losing sight of the bigger goal.

added.title: Looney Science
added.description: The Looney Builders build a science museum in the desert where Wile E. Coyote becomes distracted by the Road Runner.

added.title: Silly Hat Catastrophe!/Zee In A Bottle
added.description: Lloyd is selling silly hats at the factory, but when the hat machine malfunctions it starts raining silly hats on Pretty Big City!/Zee makes a giant rocket ship in a bottle, but things take a turn when he gets stuck inside!

added.title: MacBarm's Day Off/Playhouse Problems
added.description: It's MacBarm's day off and Zee takes over harvesting carrots with his Zee mobile, but when it breaks, the work still needs to be done./Ranger Nat is bringing a playhouse on the train for Timmy and Izzy, but it won't fit through the tunnel!

added.title: Kana Recharges
added.description: Tired and in need of relaxation, Kana decides to take a well-deserved break between deliveries. When she tells Thomas that she wants time all by herself, Thomas is worried that he and the other engines have done something to upset her. Determined to right their assumed wrongs, Thomas and friends follow Kana around the island to convince her to play with them -- the exact opposite of what she needs! When a big storm reaches Sodor, Kana teaches her friends about the value of spending time alone and "feeling the hush."
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: The Big Skunk Funk
added.description: Abuzz with excitement about the Sodor Flower Festival, Thomas is given the important task of transporting Sir Topham Hatt's prized roses to the event. On the way, Thomas' sweet-smelling journey takes a turn for the stinky when a skunk crosses the tracks and sprays the engine with the funkiest scent imaginable! Now, with the help of his friends, Thomas must find a way to get rid of the stench and get to the festival on time.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: More Cowbell
added.description: Thomas is elated when he finds a cowbell on the side of the tracks, until his friends start hogging it.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Sir Topham Hatt's Hat
added.description: When Sir Topham Hatt's Hat blows away in the wind before making an important announcement, Thomas and his friends race around Sodor, trying to catch it. The Hat remains out of reach until they learn to work together.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Nia's Surprising Surprise
added.description: Nia is planning a big party to celebrate the anniversary of her arrival on Sodor, but she finds that her friends don't remember her anniversary and are too busy to even talk about it.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Halloween Party
added.description: D.BO wonders how do you throw the best Halloween party ever?

added.title: Bear Hibernation
added.description: Blippi wonders how do bears prepare for hibernation?

added.title: Fruit & Vegetables
added.description: On the hunt to discover the difference between fruits and vegetables, Blippi finds himself as a contestant in a community garden game show! Game show host Slim Cucumber quizzes Blippi on his knowledge of fruits and vegetables. Will Blippi know the answers?

added.title: Mountain
added.description: Blippi and TABBS head off on an icy adventure and fly up the side of Mt. Everest, the world's tallest mountain! They are joined by Betty the Yeti who is climbing to the top of the mountain in search of the ultimate snack - fresh snow!

added.title: Chocolate Factory
added.description: Blippi's love for chocolate makes him wonder "How are chocolate bars made?" They head into a chocolate factory to find out, get a tour from Bard the Chocolate Bar, and FETCH gets a close-up look at the chocolate-making process!

added.title: Get Active Dance
added.description: Mei, Ella, animals and vegetables have a farm active day exercising and organising the farm

added.title: Baa Baa Black Sheep
added.description: It's getting chilly on the farm! Summers dwindled into autumn and everyone is in need of some winter clothing

added.title: Splash Song
added.description: Ella is drawing a bus when she lets her imagination runs wild!

added.title: The Silly Little song
added.description: The other children and the animals all get together to cheer Rishi up with a funny, silly song.

added.title: The Penguin Dance
added.description: Rico the penguin is visiting Lellobee city farm… and he's travelled all the way from the North pole!

added.title: Mine!
added.description: Daffy learns a lesson in doing the right thing when he finds a purse filled with money.

added.title: Sylvester the Pester
added.description: An attention-starved Sylvester won't let Granny have any time to herself.

added.title: Cat-Taz-Trophy
added.description: Sylvester and Taz team up to win a toy racecar derby.

added.title: Duck! Monster! Duck!
added.description: Daffy reads the babies a scary story, only to end up frightening himself.

added.title: The Brave Little Tweety
added.description: Tweety takes a role in a play too seriously and begins to believe he's a real superhero.
